Kogi State Governor Yahaya Bello has approved the appointment of Pharm Abdulkareem Jamiu as his new Chief of Staff. A statement issued yesterday by Secretary to the Government of Kogi State, Mrs Folashade Ayoade-Arike, said the appointment followed the resignation of Chief Edward Onoja as Chief of Staff to the governor. She said Jamiu, until his appointment, was the Director General, Protocol to the governor. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY The statement also said that the governor has approved the appointment of Dr Gabriel Ottah as the new Director General, Protocol to the governor. She said both appointments take effective from October 14. Kogi governor names new Chief of staff as Onoja resigns Kogi guber: Why Bello picked Onoja as running mate Yobe governor appoints chief of staff